ing any of the selection boxes on the left. You can choose as many of these selections as you desire. Keep in mind, though, that if you are too specific you may not find any items meeting your search requirements.<br><br>For example, when you select 1H Slash you will probably see a rather long list when you click Find. You might choose to narrow that down by selecting Vah Shir in the Select by Race box (keeping the 1H Slash selection). That would restrict the listed items to 1H Slashing weapons usable by Vah Shir. But if you also require that the item be equipable in the Ranged slot, you might find that no items match your search.<br><br>If you want to clear the selections you’ve made for your search criteria, click the Reset button.<br><br>Once you have a list of items that interests you, you can right click on any item on the list to see information about that item.<br><br> <br><br>The list of merchants is updated when first enter the Bazaar. The Update Traders button will update the list of Traders for your selection in the Traders box. However, whenever you search for items, all available items are checked.<br><br>Once you have located the item you are looking for and chosen a trader to buy it from, you will only need to find that trader and finalize the deal.<br><br>You can find any trader on your list by right-clicking on his name in the item list. Your character will turn to face the character whose name you have clicked on. This makes locating your merchant an easy task.<br><br>Once you have located your merchant, simply right-click on him. You can interact with a player merchant in exactly the same way that you interact with an NPC merchant.<br><br> <br><br>In order to become a Trader in the Bazaar you will need a Trader’s Satchel. You can purchase these from NPC merchants in the Bazaar. Place items that you wish to sell into the Trader’s Satchel. Only items in your Trader’s Satchels can be sold, and only from those satchels that you have on you (you can’t sell items out of your bank).<br><br>Also, in order to become a trader you will need to be inside one of the many stalls in the Bazaar.<br><br>Typing /trader opens up the Bazaar Vendor window.<br><br> <br><br>When you open this window it will check to see what items you were selling last and uses pricing information that was stored to set prices on those items. It will also show you all the items in Trader’s Satchel that you can sell (note: it will not display no-drop items). Items added to the satchel after this window is open will not show. You will have to reopen the window if you want to see those items.<br><br>This is where you set the prices for your items. To do so, just click on the item. Then click on the appropriate coin(s) and type in the amount you wish to charge for the item. Once you have the proper price showing in the coin list, just click on the Set Price button. You will see a message with the item name and price in the window.<br><br>You can clear the price of any item by selecting that item and clicking on the Clear Price button.<br><br>Once you have set the price on your items, you are ready to sell them.<br><br>In order to be a Trader you must be in one of the stalls in the Bazaar. Once there, click the Begin Trader button and your items will be available for purchase by other player characters.<br><br>If you want to make an item on your list unavailable for sale you can click on the item and then click the Remove button. This will take the item off of your trader list and it will be unavailable for sale. To put the item back up for sale, just select it and click on the Add button.<br><br>Items that are for sale will be highlighted in green in your Trader Window. Leaving the stall area will automatically turn off your Trader status.<br><br> <br><br>The List Items button prints out a list of all of the items you have for sale in the window.<br><br>Enjoy your time in the Bazaar.<br> <p><center>I'm n